erything (maybe positive), but egocentric contradictory. Professional development lacking.\n\nCandidate D:\nPositives: responds to unexpected events adequately, concentrates well, solves problems extremely well, takes responsibility seriously, good problem solving, concentration, responsibility. Negatives: moody, loner, arrogant, hot temper, know-it-all, weak leadership, considered moody, loner (teamwork). Professional development unknown.\n\nWe need to weigh. For long-distance flights, reliability, calmness, decision-making, teamwork crucial. Candidate C seems strong on reliability, calmness, decision-making, crew atmosphere, technical competence. Communication difficulty and egocentric may be mitigated? But egocentric could affect crew. However positive crew atmosphere suggests good teamwork despite egocentric? Might be contradictory.\n\nCandidate B strong on stress handling, conscientiousness, technical weather assessment, but communication issues and pretentiousness.\n\nCandidate A strong technical vision, anticipates danger, leadership, but health and unfriendly.\n\nCandidate D strong problem solving, responsibility, concentration, but moody, loner, hot temper.\n\nThus likely candidate C is best overall, despite lack of professional development. But long-term suitability may be a concern. However long-distance pilot may need ongoing training; C not willing to further education could be a risk. B also not explicit about development. D also unknown. A also not open to new ideas.\n\nMaybe we need more info about professional development for B, D. Could ask other agents about any evidence of professional development for B or D. Also ask about health of A (eats unhealthily) maybe impact reliability.\n\nWe can ask: Agent 1 or 2 if they have any info on candidate B's professional development or training attitude, and candidate D's teamwork/communication specifics.\n\nWe have limited turn: we can ask one question to each agent. Let's ask Agent 1: any info on candidate 